beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Nice cloudy pale pour with good head.  Spice with nice balance of bitters and citrus.
Beautiful looking dark beer with a nice head to start.  Head left quick, but flavor is good.  Balanced and smooth there is a hint of sweetness and a nice velvety texture.

Nice bold flavor.  A very sweet stout that packs a punch.  Caramel and vanilla are strong, even overpowering, but slight bitterness and dark stout flavor helps to temper it.  The brewery will not let  you take growlers of this home!  I voiced my dissatisfaction.
Very unique flavor.  I have never had a beer quite like this.  Nice sweet flavor with balanced bitterness of an imperial stout.  Easy to drink.
Faint malty sweet aroma.  Smooth with a nice sweet roasted malt taste.  A little unrefined, and could be thicker.  Very easy to drink with just enough ABV kick.

Starts dark with a bitter opening followed by spices and a sweet fruit ending with a slight bitter after taste.  
Pours a nice head and is redish brown in color.  I would like a little more spice and less of the bitterness.
beer_name: Laughing Dog Cold Nose Winter Ale

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Sweet with heavy hazel and maple aromas.  It has a nice toasted finish that is sweet the whole way through.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: A balanced bock.  That said it lacks the heavy malty sweetness characteristic of the style.  While the caramel malt comes through with a sweet malt flavor there is a hopped finish that it uncharacteristic of bocks.  I liked the beer but expected less hopps and more malt.  Wonderful head forms in the glass.
